IRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of uncertain origin, perhaps from Latin <i>sanctus</i> ‘holy’. It will always be associated with  Sancho Panza ,  Don Quixote's  companion."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sanche Carew was born in 1457, in Purley on Thames, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Nicholas Carew, Esq. III, was 18 and her mother, Margaret Langford, was 19. She married Sir John Iwardby about 1485. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died about 1510, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 54."},"et":{"1457–Abt 1510":"1457–umbes 1510","1457–1510":"1457–1510","1460–Female":"1460–Surnud","1463–1474":"1463–1474","1466–1485":"1466–1485","1440–1525":"1440–1525","1477–1553":"1477–1553","1440–1466":"1440–1466","1438–1501":"1438–1501","before 1454":"enne 1454","1440":"1440","1460":"1460","Abt 1510":"umbes 1510","1525":"1525","1457":"1457","1501":"1501","1466":"1466","1477":"1477","1510":"1510","1553":"1553","1485":"1485","1474":"1474","1463":"1463","about 1485":"umbes 1485","1438":"1438","Purley on Thames, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Purley on Thames, Berkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Quainton, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Quainton, Buckinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Beddington, Surrey, England":"Beddington, Surrey, England","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1457–Abt 1510":"1457–noin 1510","1457–1510":"1457–1510","1460–Female":"1460–Kuollut","1463–1474":"1463–1474","1466–1485":"1466–1485","1440–1525":"1440–1525","1477–1553":"1477–1553","1440–1466":"1440–1466","1438–1501":"1438–1501","before 1454":"ennen vuotta 1454","1440":"1440","1460":"1460","Abt 1510":"noin 1510","1525":"1525","1457":"1457","1501":"1501","1466":"1466","1477":"1477","1510":"1510","1553":"1553","1485":"1485","1474":"1474","1463":"1463","about 1485":"noin 1485","1438":"1438","Purley on Thames, Berkshire, England, United Ki